[Western Visayas, one of the regions of the Philippines, is designated
as Region VI. It consists of 6 provinces; Aklan, Antique, Negros
Occidental, Capiz, Guimaras, and Iloilo and 16 cities making it the
region with the highest number of cities. Iloilo City is the regional
center. The location and provinces of Western Visayas can be seen on
the map at
http://mapsof.net/uploads/static-maps/philippines_regions_and_provinces.png.
A HealthMap/ProMED-mail interactive map of the Philippines can be seen
at http://healthmap.org/r/1hsS.

Since children apparently are the most frequent victims of rabies
virus infection in Western Visayas, the priority being given to
inclusion of rabies education in the school curriculum should reduce
the overall human death rate. Progress in control of rabies in Western
Visayas has been impressive. However, final eradication of rabies
virus infection will require a more intensive and extensive dog
control programme. - Mod.CP]
